cs.LG, cs.NA, cs.CV, cs.DS, cs.IT 

This paper focuses on accelerating matrix completion using randomized singular value decomposition (rSVD), which is a popular technique in machine learning and computer vision. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) since matrix completion is often used in these fields. The paper also discusses the use of eigSVD and subspace recycling techniques, which are related to numerical analysis and optimization, making cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) a likely category as well. Finally, the paper involves computational complexity analysis and optimization, which falls under cs.IT (Information Theory).
